President Obama called South African President Jacob Zuma to express his condolences on the death of Former President Nelson Mandela. Obama spoke about how Mandela's example of moral courage, kindness, and humility influenced his own life and the lives of millions around the world. He also reaffirmed the strong partnership between the United States and South Africa, and emphasized the importance of promoting equality, reconciliation, human dignity, and building a more just and prosperous world.